%section#faq.py-5
  .container
    %h1 FAQ
    %h4 But I live in X...I can't get outside without driving!
    %p
      Fair enough! We can't all live in Jackson, but there are a lot of adventures you can find close to home.
      Here are a few ideas to get you started:
      %ul
        %li
          = link_to 'Strava', 'http://www.strava.com'
          is like an internet guidebook. There are helpful features like heatmaps and flybys to help you find
          what other adventurers are doing in your area, and you can search activities with keywords to try to find
          things in a particular area.
        %li
          = link_to 'Caltopo.', 'http://www.caltopo.com'
          Nothing beats a good old fashioned map! Caltopo has some great tools for working with maps
          and a number of excellent base tiles to choose from.
        %li
          = link_to 'GaiaGPS', 'https://www.gaiagps.com'
          is my favorite mobile map application with great topo maps and an extensive knowledge of trails and roads
          (even old decommissioned ones).
        %li
          = link_to 'Instagram.', 'http://www.instagram.com'
          Browsing Instagram can be a great way to discover new, local spots or get ideas on what other people are
          doing! Follow the hashtag #CarFreeChallenge and
          = link_to '@barueat', 'https://www.instagram.com/barueat/'
          to see what our community is up to!
    %h4 But really though. I can't find anything that doesn't involve driving.
    %p
      = mail_to 'nick@thecarfreechallenge.com', 'Email us'
      and we will personally help you find adventures close to home.
    %h4 What counts as "car free?"
    %p
      Great question. The short answer is, it's up to you -- this is all voluntary and self-reporting.
      For the purposes of the challenge, I'm saying
      %strong no driving.
      Meaning, you can't drive your car and you can't carpool with a friend. Mass transit is good to go -- you'd be
      surprised what awesome places subways, trains, and busses can get you to!
    %p
      Along those lines, things like gondolas, lifts, etc. are ok, but you can't count them towards your goal.
      In other words, 4 laps off the tram at Jackson is 0' towards the challenge. But if you take the tram up
      and spend your whole day earning turns in Granite Creek, that can count, as long as you didn't
      drive to the mountain.

